<author>Laura Bottino</author>
<title>Psalm 27</title>
<lyrics>[V1]
 The Lord is the light of my life
 Who shall I fear?
 Who can scare me?
 The Lord is the strenght of my life
 Who shall I fear?
 Who can scare me?
 Though my enemies surround me
 I shall not fear?
 In the battlefield

[V2]
 I will trust in your Holy name
 For You are the Lord Who is with me
 I will not be scared I will not be afraid
 In my heart I will trust in You Lord

[V3]
 My heart longs to dwell in Your house
 To behold your beauty fully in awe of You
 You will spare me from evil in adversity
 In Your dwelling place You will hide me

[V4]
 Hear me oh God
 I lift up my voice
 Searching out for You
 Come close to me

[V5]
 Put your hope in God
 Remain firm in Him
 Put your hope in God
 With all your heart
 Put your hope in Him</lyrics>
</song>